    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-25T08:00:00-05:00" n="397"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">501.BC Indonesia/11–2549: Circular telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Offices</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d397fn1">At 14 posts (Afghanistan, Australia, Burma, Egypt,
                        Ethiopia, India, Iran, Iraq, Lebanon, Pakistan, Saudi Arabia and Yemen,
                        Syria, Philippines, Siam); and repeated in airgram A–145, November 29, to
                        Ceylon.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-25T08:00:00-05:00"
                            >November 25, 1949—8 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In Usgadel No. 112 Nov 23, 1949 <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> outlined to
                    US Del <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> and US <gloss target="#t_Rep1"
                        >Rep</gloss>
                    <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> certain principles governing treatment of
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> case in forthcoming discussion <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> and <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss>. [Here
                    follows report and summary of telegram printed <hi rend="italic"
                    >supra</hi>.]</p>
                <p>In ur discretion inform <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> substance US
                    position this matter, <pb facs="0590" n="576" xml:id="pg_576"/> emphasizing
                    desirability strong support New Delhi group for new <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> nation, and suggesting that such assistance can be given
                    helpful initial impetus by expression approval in UN.</p>
                <p>Ur comments <gloss target="#t_FonOff1">FonOff</gloss> reactions requested.<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d397fn2">A circular telegram of December 1, 2 p. m., to the
                        above 14 posts (other than Australia) and to New Zealand quoted comment from
                        the <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> (telegram 1386, December 1, from
                        New York) that the Australian delegation had been instructed to negotiate a
                        resolution, to be cosponsored by 16 New Delhi powers, congratulating the
                            <gloss target="#t_RTC1">RTC</gloss> parties on their success and making
                        it clear the Indonesian case should not be kept on the agenda. (501.BC
                        Indonesia/12–149)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
